  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Naturopath_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb0d4fc675c71120</T>
      <T n="text">0xC51944D3<!--The <font color="#199C2C"><b>Naturopath Career</b></font> is all about holistic, interpersonal care for other Sims! Treat clients by crafting <font color="#199C2C"><b>Cures</b></font> for <font color="#199C2C"><b>Ailments</b></font>, or help them navigate everyday emotional and physical distress, improving their <font color="#199C2C"><b>Balance</b></font>.\n\nJoin the Naturopath Career by selecting the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Phone</b></font> and locating the Business Icon. Once selected, choose Find Job and select <font color="#199C2C"><b>Naturopath Career</b></font>.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Naturopath_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb0d4fc675c71123</T>
      <T n="text">0xF6ECC989<!--Sims in this career have flexible options for the workday. They can stay home and do standard Work From Home assignments, Go to Work alone, or take PTO.\n\nStarting at Level 2 of the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Naturopath Career</b></font>, Sims can also See Clients on their home lot! Stay with your Sim during their work day and help them diagnose and treat the client Sim who comes to the home lot for that day.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Naturopath_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb0d4fc675c71122</T>
      <T n="text">0xEBAB4B<!--When opting to See Clients at Home, a client Sim will arrive at the home lot with either an Ailment or distress—either physical or emotional. The Naturopath's job is to figure out which!\n\nStart by inviting the Client in, then get to work assessing them to find the Root Cause of their visit. <font color="#199C2C"><b>Conduct Client Intake</b></font>, and then Ask and Discuss a variety of things to eliminate possible causes. <font color="#199C2C"><b>Holistically Examine</b></font> the Client to unlock clues about their condition. Sims with Ailments will show physical signs, like changes to their skin or effects on objects and Sims around them, which can help quickly narrow things down.\n\n<font color="#199C2C"><b>Discuss the Root Cause</b></font> with the Client after gathering enough information, then offer them treatment—that could be a crafted Cure, or even <font color="#199C2C"><b>Providing Emotional Regulation</b></font>.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Naturopath_Slide4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fb0d4fc675c71125</T>
      <T n="text">0xB0AD5940<!--Following the Goals in the upper left side of the screen will ensure success! Jumping straight to an accurate diagnosis will earn the minimum score, but the best Naturopaths really take time to listen and show Clients they care. Use the Goals as a guide to reach Gold and enjoy the benefits of a job well done!\n\nKeep in mind that using the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Ask</b></font> or <font color="#199C2C"><b>Discuss</b></font> interactions under <font color="#199C2C"><b>Client Assessment</b></font> in the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Naturopath Care</b></font> category will continue to narrow down the possibilities, even after completing the goals leading up to Identify Root Cause.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
